data.title: Furniture and Mattress Store Near Me
data.meta_description: Shop for furniture, mattresses, and home décor at your Greenwood, SC Ashley Store. Visit our showroom today to furnish your home affordably.
data.text:
We purchased a new queen bedroom set in January of 2024. The set took almost 6 months to arrive and when it did the 2 nightstands were the wrong ones and the head board had a 12 inch scratch across it. Recently we discovered wood chips below the bed which turned out to be from broken mattress supports which were not properly anchored by their installers. After 7 months I am still waiting for a new headboard and support frame. After spending over $4800 on a new bed set I am still waiting to be made whole. I will; never buy another piece of furniture from them and would highly recommend any one looking for new furniture to consider anyone else but Ashley.

I wish I could give zero stars but there is no such thing on Google..I bought a expensive bedroom set from Ashley with the intention of leaving the items in the box due to a pending move. My sales rep KC knew this and even called the warehouse manage to confirm that they would remain boxed. When I arrived at my new house and unpacked the headboard, I found it to be damaged. I contacted my sales rep but never got a returned phone call. I then called and emailed customer service and after waiting a day Ashley denied all responsibility because I failed to inspect the boxes – they had no marks on them – when they were delivered and also because I moved. Well the whole purpose of leaving the furniture in the boxes was to protect it during the move. My salesperson never informed me that I would have no recourse if the items were damaged. Never do business with this company as they are dishonest and do not stand behind their products.

This business is a sham. Let me just walk you through what has been a nearly three-month ordeal with this company. This nightmare of a journey starts on 10/31/2023. I show up to the store to purchase a bedroom set. Over two hours later, I finally have been able to checkout, requiring not only a sales associate to figure out how to do this, but also someone from leadership. I had added on an in-store item, which they could not figure out how to get on the ticket, so they just added another item of similar cost to substitute it on the ticket. I had also ordered some sconces (online price $39.99 a piece, store price $99.99 a piece). What I did not realize at the time, is that the sales associate included two sconces at each price point on the ticket. When I received these, I promptly went to return them to the store, but the store said I needed to send them back through dispatch when the next delivery came. Tried to do that, and that didn't work. After many phone calls/chats with customer service and three separate trips to the store, the store finally took them back but couldn't give me a return receipt because they would have to process it with HQ. When the return processed in January 2023 (that's right, nearly 3 months later), they only issued $149.78, rather than the full $199.99. Then, on January 22, I'm told by customer service, "Unfortunately, we would not be able to credit the additional funds as the return was completed 12/29." I reached out on 1/7, however, to confirm the details of the return because I hadn't heard from anyone and was unable to do so because it was "still processing." So, apparently, this company is just going to keep my $50 that they owe me. This is also after what was supposed to be a single delivery including all items turned into three separate deliveries without even noticing me until things showed up to the house piece by piece.

One star is actually generous. On March 6, we received two bookcases. The bookcases were both received damaged in delivery. The delivery guy just left it here and told us that someone would contact us within 48 hours on how to deal with it. Against my better judgment, we kept the pieces no one contacted us and we went to the store and complained that they took our pictures. They submitted them via email and said someone contact us. No one contacted us so I contacted them. They said they didn’t have any pictures. I sent the pictures. Since then, everyone promised to call me back and not one person ever calls back today April 11 was the day we’ve been waiting for someone to come out and look at these pieces cause they said they could not replace them and they had to repair them when I called again today. They said nothing was scheduled. Ashley does not respond to damages. They stick with these items and they lie , these items were paid and paid back paying the bill bill because they are not responding to us and it’s one lie after another lie after another lie

I had the opportunity to go in the store, and I met Susan. She was one of the sweetest sales person I've met. I was looking was looking for a certain piece of furniture, and not only did she make sure I got what I needed, her and I sat and talked as if we were old friends. She has a caring heart, and I know this by the genuine concern she showed when I explained I believe I have a slight peanut allergy (undiagnosed) but she help me realize the importance of being treated. She wasn't pushing or overbearing, which a lot of sales people can be. I even shared my testimony with her. The staff was friendly, courteous, and professional. We were able to laugh quite a bit also. Thank you Susan, your an amazing woman.

We were searching for a new couch. And Ashley helped through the entire process. The associate that helped us, Susan, was extremely nice, knowledgeable, friendly, and helped us find exactly what we were searching for. Another associate, I can’t remember his name, even took time out to befriend our son. Anyone with children knows a furniture store is like a playground to them. They were patient and kind the whole way through. They even told us about an upcoming sale and price matched what was on the Ashley website resulting in saving us hundreds of dollars. The sectional we needed to fit our space had a piece that was out of stock so delivery was going to have to be delayed which we were fine with, we were expecting a month or longer because of past dealings with other companies, but within a few days the piece was in and delivery scheduled. I highly recommend Susan and Ashley of Greenwood and will be using them again the next time we need furniture.

Happy with my furniture but the service was not good. I bought a whole bedroom suite that was a closeout. The sales lady told me that they were not able to help move it at all because it was a liability. When my husband and I went to get it, the sales guy that was there did offer to help but made it very hard for us. We were asked to take it all the way to the other end of the store to take it out because the other door was supposedly on some kind of timer. However, it wasn’t on a timer when other customers were coming in. It’s a shame there’s not better customer service when you spend so much money with a store.

My girlfriend and I went in search of a couch and were greeted by very respectful sales associates, they offered help but also gave us space and allowed us to do our own research on what couch we would like. If we had questions they would answer them. After a couple visits we decided on a couch and were helped by Lindburg who helped us understand the sales going on and understand what would help us even more in purchasing this couch. We also had the help of Taylor who finalized this sale and helped us save a lot of money. Through the whole process we were bombarded by sales members nor ignored. They gave us all the help we wanted and respected our space to make our own decision. Thank you greenwood team.
